approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `value` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

claimWithdrawalIndex(uint256).details: This function processes a withdrawal request at a given index if it is eligible for claiming. It transfers the corresponding TON or WTON to the caller.

params._index: The index of the withdrawal request to claim.

claimWithdrawalTotal().details: This function processes all withdrawal requests that are eligible for claiming. It transfers the corresponding TON or WTON to the caller.

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation.

depositWTONAndGetWSTON(uint256,bool).details: Deposits WTON and mints WSTON for the sender.

params._amount: The amount of WTON to deposit.

depositWTONAndGetWSTONTo(address,uint256.details: Deposits WTON and mints WSTON for a specified address.

params._amount: The amount of WTON to deposit.
params._to: The address that will receive the minted WSTON.

getTotalClaimableAmountByUser(address).details: Iterates over the user's withdrawal requests to sum up the amounts that are eligible for claiming.

params.user: The address of the user for whom the claimable amount is calculated.

returns.totalClaimableAmount: The total amount that can be claimed by the specified user.

params._depositManager: The address of the DepositManager contract.
params._layer2Address: The address of the Layer 2 contract.
params._name: The name of the ERC20 token.
params._seigManager: The address of the SeigManager contract.
params._symbol: The symbol of the ERC20 token.
params._ton: The address of the TON token contract.
params._wton: The address of the WTON token contract.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

onApprove(address,address,uint256,bytes).details: Handles the deposits callback for TON or WTON tokens.

params._to: The address to which the tokens are approved.

returns._0: Returns true if the operation is successful.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: Pauses the contract, preventing certain functions from being called. Can only be called by the owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

requestWithdrawal(uint256).custom:events: Emits a `WithdrawalRequested` event upon successful request.
requestWithdrawal(uint256).custom:requirements: The caller must have a balance of at least `_wstonAmount` WSTON. The contract must not be paused.
requestWithdrawal(uint256).custom:reverts: Reverts if the caller does not have enough WSTON balance.
requestWithdrawal(uint256).details: This function allows users to request a withdrawal of their WSTON tokens. The withdrawal will be processed after a delay specified by the DepositManager.

params._wstonAmount: The amount of WSTON to withdraw.

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `value`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `value`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `value`.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause().details: Unpauses the contract, allowing certain functions to be called. Can only be called by the owner.

updateSeigniorage().details: This function interacts with the SeigManager to update the seigniorage for the specified Layer 2 address. It is used to ensure that the staking rewards are up-to-date.

returns._0: bool Returns true if the seigniorage update is successful.

claimWithdrawalIndex(uint256).notice: Claims a specific withdrawal request for the caller by index. User gets TON only

claimWithdrawalTotal().notice: Claims all eligible withdrawal requests for the caller. User gets TON only

getTotalClaimableAmountByUser(address).notice: Calculates the total claimable amount for a specific user.

processWithdrawalRequest(uint256).notice: process one or multiple requests. This function can be called by anyone

setDepositManagerAddress(address).notice: function to update the depositManager contract address

setMaxNumWithdrawal(uint8).notice: function to update the maxNumWithdrawal variable

setSeigManagerAddress(address).notice: function to update the seigManager contract address

updateSeigniorage().notice: Updates the seigniorage for the Layer 2 staking contract.
